threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary exhibits multiple behaviors characteristic of Linux malware, particularly IoT-focused botnets. Key indicators include: 1) String Obfuscation: Function sub_10abe implements a XOR-based decryption routine using the key 0x5a to hide internal strings. 2) System Call Abstraction: The binary utilizes a custom syscall wrapper via gsbase + 0x10, likely to bypass standard library monitoring or security hooks. 3) Stealthy File Access: Function sub_13620 dynamically constructs paths to '/proc/self/fd/', a technique used to manipulate file descriptors and execute or read data from memory-backed files. 4) Manual Symbol Resolution: The sample performs manual resolution of vDSO symbols (sub_15740) and implements complex memory mapping and ELF-like header parsing (sub_1345c), typical of self-unpacking or custom-loading malware.
